{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_16","type":"command_execution","command":"/run/current-system/sw/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,260p' /root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/run.rs\"","aggregated_output":"use clap::{Args, Subcommand};\n\nuse crate::adapters::fs::{\n    FsArtifactStore, FsJournalStore, FsProjectStore, FsRawOutputStore, FsRunSnapshotStore,\n    FsRuntimeLogStore, FsSessionStore,\n};\nuse crate::adapters::stub_backend::StubBackendAdapter;\nuse crate::contexts::agent_execution::service::AgentExecutionService;\nuse crate::contexts::project_run_record::service::{self, ProjectStorePort};\nuse crate::contexts::workspace_governance;\nuse crate::shared::error::{AppError, AppResult};\n\n#[derive(Debug, Args)]\npub struct RunCommand {\n    #[command(subcommand)]\n    pub command: RunSubcommand,\n}\n\n#[derive(Debug, Subcommand)]\npub enum RunSubcommand {\n    Start,\n    Resume,\n    Status,\n    History,\n    Tail {\n        #[arg(long)]\n        logs: bool,\n    },\n    Rollback {\n        #[arg(long)]\n        to: String,\n        #[arg(long)]\n        hard: bool,\n    },\n}\n\npub async fn handle(command: RunCommand) -> AppResult<()> {\n    match command.command {\n        RunSubcommand::Status => handle_status().await,\n        RunSubcommand::History => handle_history().await,\n        RunSubcommand::Tail { logs } => handle_tail(logs).await,\n        RunSubcommand::Start => Err(AppError::NotYetImplemented {\n            command: \"run start\".to_owned(),\n        }),\n        RunSubcommand::Resume => Err(AppError::NotYetImplemented {\n            command: \"run resume\".to_owned(),\n        }),\n        RunSubcommand::Rollback { .. } => Err(AppError::NotYetImplemented {\n            command: \"run rollback\".to_owned(),\n        }),\n    }\n}\n\npub fn build_agent_execution_service(\n) -> AgentExecutionService<StubBackendAdapter, FsRawOutputStore, FsSessionStore> {\n    AgentExecutionService::new(\n        StubBackendAdapter::default(),\n        FsRawOutputStore,\n        FsSessionStore,\n    )\n}\n\nasync fn handle_status() -> AppResult<()> {\n    let current_dir = std::env::current_dir()?;\n\n    let config = workspace_governance::load_workspace_config(&current_dir)?;\n    workspace_governance::ensure_supported_workspace_version(&config)?;\n\n    let project_id = workspace_governance::resolve_active_project(&current_dir)?;\n\n    // Validate canonical project record before proceeding with run queries\n    let project_store = FsProjectStore;\n    let _ = project_store.read_project_record(&current_dir, &project_id)?;\n\n    let run_store = FsRunSnapshotStore;\n    let status = service::run_status(&run_store, &current_dir, &project_id)?;\n\n    println!(\"Project: {}\", status.project_id);\n    println!(\"Status: {}\", status.status);\n    if let Some(ref stage) = status.stage {\n        println!(\"Stage: {}\", stage);\n    }\n    if let Some(cycle) = status.cycle {\n        println!(\"Cycle: {}\", cycle);\n    }\n    if let Some(round) = status.completion_round {\n        println!(\"Completion round: {}\", round);\n    }\n    println!(\"Summary: {}\", status.summary);\n\n    Ok(())\n}\n\nasync fn handle_history() -> AppResult<()> {\n    let current_dir = std::env::current_dir()?;\n\n    let config = workspace_governance::load_workspace_config(&current_dir)?;\n    workspace_governance::ensure_supported_workspace_version(&config)?;\n\n    let project_id = workspace_governance::resolve_active_project(&current_dir)?;\n\n    // Validate canonical project record before proceeding with run queries\n    let project_store = FsProjectStore;\n    let _ = project_store.read_project_record(&current_dir, &project_id)?;\n\n    let journal_store = FsJournalStore;\n    let artifact_store = FsArtifactStore;\n\n    let history = service::run_history(&journal_store, &artifact_store, &current_dir, &project_id)?;\n\n    println!(\"Project: {}\", history.project_id);\n    println!(\"--- Journal Events ---\");\n    for event in &history.events {\n        println!(\n            \"  [{}] {} - {:?}\",\n            event.sequence, event.timestamp, event.event_type\n        );\n    }\n\n    if !history.payloads.is_empty() {\n        println!(\"--- Payloads ---\");\n        for payload in &history.payloads {\n            println!(\n                \"  {} ({}, cycle {}, attempt {})\",\n                payload.payload_id, payload.stage_id, payload.cycle, payload.attempt\n            );\n        }\n    }\n\n    if !history.artifacts.is_empty() {\n        println!(\"--- Artifacts ---\");\n        for artifact in &history.artifacts {\n            println!(\n                \"  {} (payload: {}, stage: {})\",\n                artifact.artifact_id, artifact.payload_id, artifact.stage_id\n            );\n        }\n    }\n\n    Ok(())\n}\n\nasync fn handle_tail(include_logs: bool) -> AppResult<()> {\n    let current_dir = std::env::current_dir()?;\n\n    let config = workspace_governance::load_workspace_config(&current_dir)?;\n    workspace_governance::ensure_supported_workspace_version(&config)?;\n\n    let project_id = workspace_governance::resolve_active_project(&current_dir)?;\n\n    // Validate canonical project record before proceeding with run queries\n    let project_store = FsProjectStore;\n    let _ = project_store.read_project_record(&current_dir, &project_id)?;\n\n    let journal_store = FsJournalStore;\n    let artifact_store = FsArtifactStore;\n    let log_store = FsRuntimeLogStore;\n\n    let tail = service::run_tail(\n        &journal_store,\n        &artifact_store,\n        &log_store,\n        &current_dir,\n        &project_id,\n        include_logs,\n    )?;\n\n    println!(\"Project: {}\", tail.project_id);\n    println!(\"--- Durable History ---\");\n    for event in &tail.events {\n        println!(\n            \"  [{}] {} - {:?}\",\n            event.sequence, event.timestamp, event.event_type\n        );\n    }\n\n    if !tail.payloads.is_empty() {\n        println!(\"--- Payloads ---\");\n        for payload in &tail.payloads {\n            println!(\n                \"  {} ({}, cycle {}, attempt {})\",\n                payload.payload_id, payload.stage_id, payload.cycle, payload.attempt\n            );\n        }\n    }\n\n    if !tail.artifacts.is_empty() {\n        println!(\"--- Artifacts ---\");\n        for artifact in &tail.artifacts {\n            println!(\n                \"  {} (payload: {}, stage: {})\",\n                artifact.artifact_id, artifact.payload_id, artifact.stage_id\n            );\n        }\n    }\n\n    if let Some(ref logs) = tail.runtime_logs {\n        println!(\"--- Runtime Logs ---\");\n        if logs.is_empty() {\n            println!(\"  (no runtime logs)\");\n        } else {\n            for log in logs {\n                println!(\n                    \"  [{}] {:?} [{}] {}\",\n                    log.timestamp, log.level, log.source, log.message\n                );\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    Ok(())\n}\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_15","type":"command_execution","command":"/run/current-system/sw/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,320p' /root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/project_run_record/model.rs\"","aggregated_output":"use chrono::{DateTime, Utc};\nuse serde::{Deserialize, Serialize};\n\nuse crate::shared::domain::{FlowPreset, ProjectId, StageCursor, StageId};\n\n/// Immutable project metadata persisted in `project.toml`.\n#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq, Serialize, Deserialize)]\npub struct ProjectRecord {\n    pub id: ProjectId,\n    pub name: String,\n    pub flow: FlowPreset,\n    pub prompt_reference: String,\n    pub prompt_hash: String,\n    pub created_at: DateTime<Utc>,\n    pub status_summary: ProjectStatusSummary,\n}\n\n#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq, Serialize, Deserialize)]\n#[serde(rename_all = \"snake_case\")]\npub enum ProjectStatusSummary {\n    Created,\n    Active,\n    Completed,\n    Failed,\n}\n\n/// Canonical run state persisted in `run.json`.\n/// This is the single source of truth for run progression - never inferred from artifacts.\n#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq, Serialize, Deserialize)]\npub struct RunSnapshot {\n    pub active_run: Option<ActiveRun>,\n    pub status: RunStatus,\n    pub cycle_history: Vec<CycleHistoryEntry>,\n    pub completion_rounds: u32,\n    pub rollback_point_meta: RollbackPointMeta,\n    pub amendment_queue: AmendmentQueueState,\n    pub status_summary: String,\n}\n\nimpl RunSnapshot {\n    pub fn initial() -> Self {\n        Self {\n            active_run: None,\n            status: RunStatus::NotStarted,\n            cycle_history: Vec::new(),\n            completion_rounds: 0,\n            rollback_point_meta: RollbackPointMeta::default(),\n            amendment_queue: AmendmentQueueState::default(),\n            status_summary: \"not started\".to_owned(),\n        }\n    }\n\n    pub fn has_active_run(&self) -> bool {\n        self.active_run.is_some()\n    }\n\n    /// Semantic validation of run snapshot consistency.\n    /// Returns `Err` with a description if status and active_run are inconsistent.\n    pub fn validate_semantics(&self) -> Result<(), String> {\n        match (&self.status, &self.active_run) {\n            // Running or Paused requires an active run cursor\n            (RunStatus::Running, None) => Err(\n                \"status is 'running' but active_run is null — inconsistent canonical state\"\n                    .to_owned(),\n            ),\n            (RunStatus::Paused, None) => Err(\n                \"status is 'paused' but active_run is null — inconsistent canonical state\"\n                    .to_owned(),\n            ),\n            // NotStarted must not have an active run cursor\n            (RunStatus::NotStarted, Some(_)) => Err(\n                \"status is 'not_started' but active_run is present — inconsistent canonical state\"\n                    .to_owned(),\n            ),\n            // All other combinations are valid:\n            // NotStarted + None, Running/Paused + Some, Completed/Failed + None/Some\n            _ => Ok(()),\n        }\n    }\n}\n\n#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq, Serialize, Deserialize)]\npub struct ActiveRun {\n    pub run_id: String,\n    pub stage_cursor: StageCursor,\n    pub started_at: DateTime<Utc>,\n}\n\n#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq, Serialize, Deserialize)]\n#[serde(rename_all = \"snake_case\")]\npub enum RunStatus {\n    NotStarted,\n    Running,\n    Paused,\n    Completed,\n    Failed,\n}\n\nimpl RunStatus {\n    /// Human-readable status string for CLI output.\n    pub fn display_str(self) -> &'static str {\n        match self {\n            Self::NotStarted => \"not started\",\n            Self::Running => \"running\",\n            Self::Paused => \"paused\",\n            Self::Completed => \"completed\",\n            Self::Failed => \"failed\",\n        }\n    }\n}\n\n/// A single entry in the cycle history tracking progression through work cycles.\n#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq, Serialize, Deserialize)]\npub struct CycleHistoryEntry {\n    pub cycle: u32,\n    pub stage_id: StageId,\n    pub started_at: DateTime<Utc>,\n    pub completed_at: Option<DateTime<Utc>>,\n}\n\n/// Rollback-point metadata tracked in the canonical run snapshot.\n#[derive(Debug, Clone, Default, PartialEq, Serialize, Deserialize)]\npub struct RollbackPointMeta {\n    pub last_rollback_id: Option<String>,\n    pub rollback_count: u32,\n}\n\n/// Amendment queue state tracked in the canonical run snapshot.\n#[derive(Debug, Clone, Default, PartialEq, Serialize, Deserialize)]\npub struct AmendmentQueueState {\n    pub pending: Vec<serde_json::Value>,\n    pub processed_count: u32,\n}\n\n/// A single journal event stored in `journal.ndjson`.\n#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq, Serialize, Deserialize)]\npub struct JournalEvent {\n    pub sequence: u64,\n    pub timestamp: DateTime<Utc>,\n    pub event_type: JournalEventType,\n    pub details: serde_json::Value,\n}\n\n#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq, Eq, Serialize, Deserialize)]\n#[serde(rename_all = \"snake_case\")]\npub enum JournalEventType {\n    ProjectCreated,\n    RunStarted,\n    StageEntered,\n    StageCompleted,\n    CycleAdvanced,\n    CompletionRoundAdvanced,\n    RunCompleted,\n    RunFailed,\n    RollbackCreated,\n    AmendmentQueued,\n}\n\n/// A durable history payload record stored in `history/payloads/`.\n#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq, Serialize, Deserialize)]\npub struct PayloadRecord {\n    pub payload_id: String,\n    pub stage_id: StageId,\n    pub cycle: u32,\n    pub attempt: u32,\n    pub created_at: DateTime<Utc>,\n    pub payload: serde_json::Value,\n}\n\n/// A durable history artifact record stored in `history/artifacts/`.\n#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq, Serialize, Deserialize)]\npub struct ArtifactRecord {\n    pub artifact_id: String,\n    pub payload_id: String,\n    pub stage_id: StageId,\n    pub created_at: DateTime<Utc>,\n    pub content: String,\n}\n\n/// A runtime log entry stored in `runtime/logs/`.\n#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq, Serialize, Deserialize)]\npub struct RuntimeLogEntry {\n    pub timestamp: DateTime<Utc>,\n    pub level: LogLevel,\n    pub source: String,\n    pub message: String,\n}\n\n#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq, Serialize, Deserialize)]\n#[serde(rename_all = \"snake_case\")]\npub enum LogLevel {\n    Debug,\n    Info,\n    Warn,\n    Error,\n}\n\n/// Rollback metadata stored in `rollback/`.\n#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq, Serialize, Deserialize)]\npub struct RollbackPoint {\n    pub rollback_id: String,\n    pub created_at: DateTime<Utc>,\n    pub stage_id: StageId,\n    pub cycle: u32,\n    pub run_snapshot: RunSnapshot,\n}\n\n/// Empty session store for `sessions.json`.\n#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq, Serialize, Deserialize)]\npub struct SessionStore {\n    pub sessions: Vec<serde_json::Value>,\n}\n\nimpl SessionStore {\n    pub fn empty() -> Self {\n        Self {\n            sessions: Vec::new(),\n        }\n    }\n}\n\n/// Summary used in `project list` output.\n#[derive(Debug, Clone)]\npub struct ProjectListEntry {\n    pub id: ProjectId,\n    pub name: String,\n    pub flow: FlowPreset,\n    pub status_summary: ProjectStatusSummary,\n    pub created_at: DateTime<Utc>,\n    pub is_active: bool,\n}\n\n/// Detailed project view used in `project show` output.\n#[derive(Debug, Clone)]\npub struct ProjectDetail {\n    pub record: ProjectRecord,\n    pub run_snapshot: RunSnapshot,\n    pub journal_event_count: u64,\n    pub rollback_count: usize,\n    pub is_active: bool,\n}\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_17","type":"command_execution","command":"/run/current-system/sw/bin/bash -lc 'for f in $(find /root/new-ralph-burning/.ralph/projects/ralph-burning-rewrite/loops -name '\"'*-spec.md' | sort); do echo \\\"===== \"'$f\"; sed -n '\"'1,220p' \\\"\"'$f\"; done'","aggregated_output":"===== /root/new-ralph-burning/.ralph/projects/ralph-burning-rewrite/loops/001-foundation-domain-model-workspace-init-and-flow/20260311175055-spec.md\n---\nartifact: spec\nloop: 1\nproject: ralph-burning-rewrite\nbackend: claude(opus)\nrole: planner\ncreated_at: 2026-03-11T17:50:55Z\n---\n\n# Feature: Foundation — Domain Model, Workspace Init, and Flow Discovery\n\n## Description\nBootstrap the `ralph-burning` Rust binary crate with the v1 domain model, workspace initialization, and flow discovery CLI commands. This is delivery roadmap slice 1: it establishes the Cargo project, bounded-context folder skeleton, core domain types, the `ralph-burning init` command that creates a `.ralph-burning/` workspace, and `flow list` / `flow show` commands that enumerate the four built-in flow presets with their stage sequences. It also seeds the conformance test harness with initial Gherkin scenario IDs covering workspace init and flow discovery.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `ralph-burning-rewrite/Cargo.toml` compiles a binary named `ralph-burning` (edition 2021, Rust stable)\n- [ ] Dependencies include at minimum: `clap` (derive), `serde`/`serde_json`, `toml`/`toml_edit`, `thiserror`, `chrono`, and `tokio` (rt-multi-thread)\n- [ ] Source tree contains the bounded-context folder skeleton: `src/contexts/{workspace_governance, project_run_record, workflow_composition, agent_execution, requirements_drafting, automation_runtime, conformance_spec}/mod.rs` plus `src/adapters/mod.rs` and `src/shared/mod.rs`\n- [ ] Domain model types defined in `src/shared/domain.rs` (or equivalent shared module): `FlowPreset` enum (`Standard`, `QuickDev`, `DocsChange`, `CiImprovement`), `StageId` enum with all stages from all four presets, `StageCursor` struct (stage, cycle, attempt, completion_round), `ProjectId`, `RunId`, `WorkspaceConfig` struct\n- [ ] Four built-in flow presets are defined in `src/contexts/workflow_composition/` with their exact stage sequences as specified in the master prompt section 9\n- [ ] `ralph-burning init` creates `.ralph-burning/workspace.toml` with sensible defaults (version field, created timestamp) and the required subdirectory stubs (`projects/`, `requirements/`, `daemon/tasks/`, `daemon/leases/`)\n- [ ] `ralph-burning init` on an already-initialized workspace prints an error message and exits non-zero (no implicit re-init)\n- [ ] `ralph-burning flow list` prints all four preset names with a short description\n- [ ] `ralph-burning flow show <flow-id>` prints the ordered stage list, validation profile defaults (final review enabled/disabled), and stage count for the given preset\n- [ ] `ralph-burning flow show` with an invalid flow-id exits non-zero with a clear error\n- [ ] CLI top-level uses `clap` subcommand routing with placeholder subcommand stubs for all v1 commands (config, project, run, requirements, daemon, conformance) that print \"not yet implemented\" and exit non-zero\n- [ ] `tests/conformance/features/workspace_init.feature` contains Gherkin scenarios: init fresh workspace, init already-initialized workspace, init verifies directory structure\n- [ ] `tests/conformance/features/flow_discovery.feature` contains Gherkin scenarios: list all presets, show each preset, show invalid preset\n- [ ] Unit tests exist for: flow preset stage ordering, stage cursor construction invariants (monotonic cycle/completion round), workspace config serialization round-trip\n- [ ] `cargo build` succeeds with no warnings; `cargo test` passes all tests\n- [ ] `cargo clippy` reports no warnings\n\n## Files to Modify/Create\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/Cargo.toml` — new crate manifest with binary target and dependencies\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/main.rs` — async entry point, tracing init, clap CLI dispatch\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/lib.rs` — public module re-exports\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/mod.rs` — top-level clap `Cli` struct with all subcommand groups (stubs for unimplemented ones)\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/init.rs` — `ralph-burning init` implementation\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/flow.rs` — `ralph-burning flow list` and `flow show` implementation\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/config.rs` — placeholder stub\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/project.rs` — placeholder stub\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/run.rs` — placeholder stub\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/requirements.rs` — placeholder stub\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/daemon.rs` — placeholder stub\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/conformance.rs` — placeholder stub\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/mod.rs` — shared module root\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/domain.rs` — core domain types (FlowPreset, StageId, StageCursor, ProjectId, RunId, WorkspaceConfig)\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/error.rs` — shared error types using `thiserror`\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workspace_governance/mod.rs` — workspace init logic, config loading, workspace version check\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/mod.rs` — flow preset registry, stage sequence definitions\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/project_run_record/mod.rs` — module stub\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/agent_execution/mod.rs` — module stub\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/requirements_drafting/mod.rs` — module stub\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/automation_runtime/mod.rs` — module stub\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/conformance_spec/mod.rs` — module stub\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/adapters/mod.rs` — adapter module stub\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/adapters/fs.rs` — filesystem adapter for workspace creation (ports/adapters boundary)\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/workspace_init.feature` — Gherkin scenarios for init\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/flow_discovery.feature` — Gherkin scenarios for flow commands\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/domain_test.rs` — unit tests for domain types\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/flow_preset_test.rs` — unit tests for flow preset definitions\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/workspace_test.rs` — unit tests for workspace config serialization\n\n## Dependencies\n- Requires: none (first slice)\n- Blocks: slice 2 (flow preset definitions + stage contracts + renderer contracts), slice 3 (workspace governance effective config), slice 4 (project/run canonical store)\n\n---\n===== /root/new-ralph-burning/.ralph/projects/ralph-burning-rewrite/loops/002-stage-contract-registry-and-deterministic/20260311183324-spec.md\n---\nartifact: spec\nloop: 2\nproject: ralph-burning-rewrite\nbackend: codex(gpt-5.4-xhigh)\nrole: planner\ncreated_at: 2026-03-11T18:33:24Z\n---\n\nI’m reviewing `prompt.md`, the completed loop artifact, and recent git history to determine what’s already in place and what the next missing feature slice should be.\nI have the loop and commit boundaries. Next I’m reading the actual prompt/spec inputs and the rewrite code so I can separate shipped foundation work from the next missing slice.\nThe prompt lives under the existing orchestration workspace, not the rewrite tree. I’m pulling the project prompt plus loop spec and current implementation surface together now.\nThe checked-in crate is still a narrow foundation slice. I’m reading the workflow and workspace modules now to verify whether stage contracts, effective config, or any project/run persistence already slipped in before I plan the next feature.\nI’ve confirmed the current code matches the approved loop-1 foundation plus a later `flake.nix` addition. I’m checking the checkpoint diffs now so the next feature is anchored to what actually changed between planning, implementation, review, and current HEAD.\n# Feature: Stage Contract Registry and Deterministic Artifact Rendering\n\n## Description\nLoop 1 is complete: the approved artifact and git checkpoints `1dbe79b` through `60e6d0c` delivered the Rust crate skeleton, bounded-context module layout, workspace init, built-in flow discovery, and the shared `FlowPreset` / `StageId` foundation. The only later change at `cac0f25` adds `flake.nix` support and does not add workflow behavior. The next missing slice is the unfinished remainder of roadmap step 2: a `StageContract` and renderer layer for the already-defined stages. The current codebase has no stage payload schemas, no semantic validators, no failure-class mapping, and no deterministic Markdown artifact rendering, so later work on agent execution and `run start` would otherwise have no canonical contract to target.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Add a `StageContract` registry keyed by the existing `StageId`, and every stage already present in the four built-in presets resolves to exactly one contract without changing any approved flow IDs or stage ordering.\n- [ ] Introduce typed stage payload models plus JSON Schema generation/validation for all supported stages: `prompt_review`, `planning`, `implementation`, `qa`, `review`, `completion_panel`, `acceptance_qa`, `final_review`, `plan_and_implement`, `apply_fixes`, `docs_plan`, `docs_update`, `docs_validation`, `ci_plan`, `ci_update`, and `ci_validation`.\n- [ ] Planning-style contracts (`prompt_review`, `planning`, `docs_plan`, `ci_plan`) require structured problem framing, assumptions or open questions, ordered proposed work, and explicit readiness or risk fields.\n- [ ] Execution/update contracts (`implementation`, `plan_and_implement`, `apply_fixes`, `docs_update`, `ci_update`) require structured change summaries, intended or completed steps, validation evidence or plans, and outstanding-risk fields.\n- [ ] Validation/review contracts (`qa`, `docs_validation`, `ci_validation`, `acceptance_qa`, `review`, `final_review`, `completion_panel`) require an explicit outcome/decision enum plus evidence, findings or gaps, and follow-up or amendment data when the outcome is not cleanly approved.\n- [ ] Contract evaluation order is fixed: schema validation runs first, semantic validation runs only on schema-valid payloads, and rendering runs only on payloads that passed both prior steps.\n- [ ] Introduce the canonical failure-class enum needed by later slices, including `transport_failure`, `schema_validation_failure`, `domain_validation_failure`, `timeout`, `cancellation`, and `qa_review_outcome_failure`.\n- [ ] Stage contracts map non-passing QA/review/completion decisions to `qa_review_outcome_failure` without treating them as schema or domain failures.\n- [ ] State invariants for this slice are explicit: on schema failure, semantic validation and rendering do not run; on domain failure, rendering does not run; on any failure, no success bundle is returned; callers receive either `validated payload + rendered artifact` together or an error, never one without the other.\n- [ ] Markdown renderers are deterministic and stage-specific: the same validated payload always renders byte-identical output, uses canonical `cycle` terminology, and is derived only from validated structured fields rather than raw backend text.\n- [ ] Raw backend output remains diagnostic-only input to the contract evaluator and is kept separate from payload and artifact outputs so later persistence work can store diagnostics without using Markdown as protocol.\n- [ ] Add unit tests proving every stage in every built-in flow has contract coverage, schema failures short-circuit semantic validation, semantic failures short-circuit rendering, and repeated renders of the same payload are identical.\n- [ ] Add conformance scenario IDs for successful contract evaluation, schema failure, domain failure, and QA/review outcome failure so later `run start` work inherits fixed public expectations.\n- [ ] `cargo test` and `cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings` pass after the contract and renderer modules are added.\n\n## Files to Modify/Create\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/Cargo.toml` - add schema/validation dependencies needed for typed JSON Schema support\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/domain.rs` - add shared failure-class and artifact/contract identity types used across contracts\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/error.rs` - add explicit schema-validation, domain-validation, and renderer error variants\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/mod.rs` - expose the stage-contract registry alongside the existing flow definitions\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/contracts.rs` - define `StageContract`, registry lookup, contract evaluation ordering, and failure mapping\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/payloads.rs` - define typed payload structs and schema metadata for each stage or contract family\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/renderers.rs` - implement deterministic Markdown renderers from validated payloads\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit.rs` - register new unit test modules\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/stage_contract_test.rs` - cover registry completeness, validation ordering, and failure-class behavior\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/renderer_test.rs` - cover deterministic rendering and artifact content shape\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/stage_contracts.feature` - add scenario IDs describing contract success and failure behavior\n\n## Dependencies\n- Requires: Loop 1 foundation — domain model, workspace init, and flow discovery\n- Blocks: agent execution facade with structured-output guarantee, standard preset `run start` vertical path, and later retry/remediation semantics\n\n---\n===== /root/new-ralph-burning/.ralph/projects/ralph-burning-rewrite/loops/003-workspace-governance-effective-config-and-active/20260311191151-spec.md\n---\nartifact: spec\nloop: 3\nproject: ralph-burning-rewrite\nbackend: claude(opus)\nrole: planner\ncreated_at: 2026-03-11T19:11:51Z\n---\n\nNow I have a complete picture of the project state. Let me analyze and produce the next feature spec.\n\n**Completed:**\n- Loop 1 (roadmap slice 1): Foundation — domain model, workspace init, flow discovery\n- Loop 2 (roadmap slice 2): Stage contract registry and deterministic artifact rendering\n\n**Next in roadmap:** Slice 3 — Workspace governance effective config + active project resolution\n\n# Feature: Workspace Governance Effective Config and Active Project Resolution\n\n## Description\nImplement roadmap slice 3: layered workspace configuration with `config show/get/set/edit` CLI commands, and active-project resolution via the `.ralph-burning/active-project` pointer file. The existing `workspace_governance` context currently handles workspace init and config loading but has no support for effective configuration (workspace-level defaults, runtime overrides), mutable config updates, or tracking which project is currently selected. This slice fills that gap so that downstream work (project/run canonical store in slice 4, agent execution in slice 5) can resolve effective settings and know which project commands target without explicit `--id` flags.\n\nThe config surface covers keys implied by the master prompt: `prompt_review.enabled` (controls whether the optional `prompt_review` stage runs in the `standard` flow), default backend family, default model overrides, and validation strictness. The implementation stores configuration in `workspace.toml` using a structured TOML schema, resolves effective values through a defaults-then-override chain, and enforces fail-fast on unsupported workspace versions (invariant already partially present, now wired through all config-reading paths).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `workspace.toml` schema is extended with an optional `[settings]` table supporting at minimum these keys: `prompt_review.enabled` (bool, default `true`), `default_flow` (string, must be a valid `FlowPreset`, default `\"standard\"`), `default_backend` (string, optional), `default_model` (string, optional). Unknown keys in `[settings]` are preserved on round-trip (forward-compatible editing).\n- [ ] An `EffectiveConfig` struct in `workspace_governance` resolves the full configuration by merging persisted `workspace.toml` settings with compiled defaults. Every supported key has a typed accessor with a documented default value. `EffectiveConfig::load(base_dir)` is the single entry point for all config reads.\n- [ ] `ralph-burning config show` loads the workspace, checks the version (fail-fast on mismatch), and prints all effective settings as a human-readable TOML-like table showing each key, its effective value, and its source (`default` or `workspace.toml`).\n- [ ] `ralph-burning config get <key>` prints the effective value for a single key. Exits non-zero with a clear error for unknown keys.\n- [ ] `ralph-burning config set <key> <value>` validates the key name and value type, writes the updated value into `workspace.toml` under `[settings]`, and prints a confirmation. Exits non-zero for invalid keys or values (e.g., setting `default_flow` to an unknown preset).\n- [ ] `ralph-burning config edit` opens `workspace.toml` in `$EDITOR` (or `$VISUAL`, falling back to `vi`). After the editor exits, the file is re-validated; if validation fails, the user is warned on stderr and the command exits non-zero (but the file is not reverted — the user must fix manually).\n- [ ] `active-project` is a plain-text file in `.ralph-burning/` containing a single project ID (trimmed, no newline normalization issues). When absent, commands that require an active project fail with an explicit message naming `project select`.\n- [ ] `ralph-burning project select <id>` validates that the project directory `.ralph-burning/projects/<id>/` exists and contains `project.toml`, writes the ID to `active-project`, and prints a confirmation. Exits non-zero if the project does not exist.\n- [ ] A `resolve_active_project(base_dir) -> AppResult<ProjectId>` function in `workspace_governance` reads and validates `active-project`, returning a typed `ProjectId` or a descriptive error. This function is the single resolution point for all commands that operate on the current project.\n- [ ] All config and active-project commands check workspace version first and fail fast on unsupported versions (wiring the existing `ensure_supported_workspace_version` through the CLI path).\n- [ ] The filesystem adapter (`adapters/fs.rs`) gains methods for atomic config writes (write-to-temp-then-rename) and active-project file read/write, keeping side effects behind the adapter boundary.\n- [ ] Unit tests cover: `EffectiveConfig` default resolution, override merging, round-trip serialization of extended `workspace.toml`, unknown-key preservation, invalid key/value rejection, active-project read/write/missing cases.\n- [ ] Integration tests cover: `config show` output format, `config get` known and unknown keys, `config set` valid and invalid mutations, `project select` with existing and non-existing project directories.\n- [ ] Gherkin scenarios added to `tests/conformance/features/workspace_config.feature`: show effective config, get known key, get unknown key, set valid key, set invalid value, set invalid key, edit with valid result, edit with invalid result.\n- [ ] Gherkin scenarios added to `tests/conformance/features/active_project.feature`: select existing project, select non-existing project, resolve when no active project set, resolve after valid select.\n- [ ] `cargo test` and `cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings` pass after all changes.\n\n## Files to Modify/Create\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/domain.rs` — extend `WorkspaceConfig` with optional `settings: WorkspaceSettings` field; add `WorkspaceSettings` struct with typed config fields and defaults\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/error.rs` — add error variants: `UnknownConfigKey`, `InvalidConfigValue`, `NoActiveProject`, `ProjectNotFound`, `EditorFailed`\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workspace_governance/mod.rs` — add `EffectiveConfig` struct with `load()`, `get()`, `set()` methods; add `resolve_active_project()` and `set_active_project()` functions; refactor config loading to use extended schema\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workspace_governance/config.rs` — (new) effective config resolution logic, key registry, default values, validation of key names and value types\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/adapters/fs.rs` — add `write_atomic()`, `read_active_project()`, `write_active_project()`, `open_editor()` methods\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/config.rs` — implement `show`, `get`, `set`, `edit` handlers replacing the current stubs\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/project.rs` — implement `select` handler (other project subcommands remain stubs)\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/config_test.rs` — unit tests for effective config resolution, merging, serialization, key validation\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/active_project_test.rs` — unit tests for active-project read/write/missing\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/workspace_config.feature` — Gherkin scenarios for config commands\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/active_project.feature` — Gherkin scenarios for active project resolution\n\n## Dependencies\n- Requires: Loop 1 (workspace init, `WorkspaceConfig`, filesystem adapter) and Loop 2 (flow preset validation for `default_flow` config key)\n- Blocks: Slice 4 (project/run canonical store needs `resolve_active_project` and effective config), Slice 5 (agent execution needs default backend/model config resolution), Slice 6 (`run start` needs active project and effective config for prompt_review gate)\n\n---\n===== /root/new-ralph-burning/.ralph/projects/ralph-burning-rewrite/loops/004-project-and-run-record-foundation/20260311194558-spec.md\n---\nartifact: spec\nloop: 4\nproject: ralph-burning-rewrite\nbackend: codex(gpt-5.4-xhigh)\nrole: planner\ncreated_at: 2026-03-11T19:45:58Z\n---\n\nI’m reviewing `prompt.md`, the completed loop specs, and recent git checkpoints to determine what is already covered and what the next unimplemented slice should be. First I’ll map the current planning artifacts against the roadmap and the codebase state so I don’t re-spec completed work.\nI’ve confirmed the branch is sitting just after Loop 3 planning, with loops 1 through 3 committed in git and conformance coverage matching those slices. Next I’m reading the actual spec artifacts and the current Rust modules to check whether roadmap step 4 has already been partially built or only stubbed.\nThe loop artifacts live under the hidden `.ralph/` planning workspace, not in the Rust crate itself. I’m reading those specs plus the current source modules now to determine whether the next slice is the canonical project/run store from roadmap step 4 or whether some of that was already pulled forward.\nThe approved specs line up cleanly with roadmap slices 1 through 3. I’m now checking the current `project_run_record`, `project` CLI, and `run` CLI surfaces to see whether any slice-4 behavior already exists, so the next spec only covers the actual gap.\nSlice 4 is still empty in code: `project_run_record` is only a stub, `project create/list/show/delete` are unimplemented, and every `run` subcommand still exits `NotYetImplemented`. I’m confirming there isn’t hidden project/run persistence elsewhere and then I’ll draft the next feature around that gap.\nI’ve verified there’s no hidden implementation beyond Loop 3. To tighten the next spec, I’m pulling the architecture notes for the `project_run_record` context from the repo docs so the acceptance criteria line up with the intended storage model and invariants, not just the roadmap headline.\nThe roadmap and architecture notes both point to the same next gap: `Project & Run Record`. I’m pulling the scenario notes around project creation and durable-history-vs-runtime-log separation so the spec includes the right invariants for failure handling and query behavior.\nI have enough to choose the slice. I’m doing one last pass over the shared error types and current storage helpers so the file list and failure-mode criteria match the crate’s existing structure instead of inventing a parallel design.\n# Feature: Project and Run Record Foundation\n\n## Description\nLoops 1 through 3 are complete: the rewrite already has workspace bootstrap, built-in flow discovery, stage-contract/rendering infrastructure, and workspace governance with effective config plus active-project resolution. The next missing slice is roadmap step 4: make `project_run_record` the durable source of truth by implementing canonical project storage, initial run/journal state, project CRUD, and read-only run query commands.\n\nCurrent HEAD still has `src/contexts/project_run_record/mod.rs` as a stub, `project create/list/show/delete` unimplemented, and all `run` commands unimplemented. This feature should fill that gap without re-planning completed flow, config, or active-project work.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `ralph-burning project create --id <id> --name <name> --prompt <file> --flow <flow-id>` validates workspace version, project ID, flow preset, prompt readability, and duplicate IDs before any filesystem mutation.\n- [ ] Successful project creation writes `.ralph-burning/projects/<project-id>/project.toml`, `prompt.md`, `run.json`, `journal.ndjson`, `sessions.json`, `history/payloads/`, `history/artifacts/`, `runtime/logs/`, `runtime/backend/`, `runtime/temp/`, `amendments/`, and `rollback/`.\n- [ ] `project.toml` persists immutable project metadata: `id`, `name`, fixed `flow`, copied prompt reference, prompt hash, creation timestamp, and durable status summary. Flow cannot be changed after creation by any CLI or store path.\n- [ ] `run.json` persists canonical run state only: active run pointer, run status, optional stage cursor, cycle history, completion rounds, rollback-point metadata, amendment-queue state, and status summary. It must not infer state from artifacts or logs.\n- [ ] `journal.ndjson` is append-only, sequence-ordered, and initialized with a `project_created` event. Queries derive state from canonical run state plus journal, never from Markdown scans.\n- [ ] `sessions.json` initializes as a valid empty session store, separate from durable history.\n- [ ] `project create` is atomic. If prompt copy, snapshot write, or journal initialization fails, the new project is not visible to `project list/show`, no partial canonical files remain exposed, and `.ralph-burning/active-project` is unchanged.\n- [ ] Duplicate project creation fails non-zero with a clear error and leaves existing project state unchanged.\n- [ ] `project create` does not implicitly select the new project; active-project mutation remains the job of the already-implemented `project select`.\n- [ ] `ralph-burning project list` reads canonical project records, not raw directory names, and shows enough summary data to identify each project plus whether it is the active selection.\n- [ ] `ralph-burning project show [<id>]` shows explicit project data when `<id>` is provided and otherwise resolves the active project through workspace governance. Output includes flow, prompt hash/reference, created timestamp, run summary, and rollback summary.\n- [ ] `ralph-burning project delete <id>` deletes only projects with no active run. If the deleted project was selected, `.ralph-burning/active-project` is cleared only after the delete succeeds. If delete fails after validation, the project remains addressable and the active-project pointer is unchanged.\n- [ ] Add payload/artifact store models and enumeration APIs for durable history. If a payload write succeeds but its artifact companion write/index fails, `run history` and `run tail` must not expose a partial durable-history record.\n- [ ] Runtime logs are stored and queried separately from durable history. Runtime-log write failures must not fabricate, remove, or reorder durable history.\n- [ ] `ralph-burning run status` reads canonical state for the active project and reports either “not started” or the persisted run snapshot without inferring from artifacts.\n- [ ] `ralph-burning run history` shows durable history only: journal events plus payload/artifact records in canonical order. Runtime logs never appear there.\n- [ ] `ralph-burning run tail` shows durable history only by default, and `ralph-burning run tail --logs` appends the newest runtime logs after the durable section without changing the durable-history portion.\n- [ ] Corrupt or inconsistent canonical files (`project.toml`, `run.json`, `journal.ndjson`, payload/artifact indexes) fail fast with file-specific errors. Commands must not fall back to rendered Markdown or directory scans when canonical state is invalid.\n- [ ] Introduce `ProjectStorePort`, `JournalStorePort`, `ArtifactStorePort`, and `RuntimeLogStorePort` boundaries inside `contexts/project_run_record`, with filesystem-backed adapters using atomic writes/renames.\n- [ ] Add domain/unit tests for immutable flow, journal sequencing, and history/log separation; service tests with fake ports; adapter contract tests for filesystem round trips and corruption visibility; and CLI integration tests for project CRUD plus run queries.\n- [ ] Add public Gherkin coverage for project creation, duplicate IDs, immutable flow, list/show/delete behavior, no-active-run status, durable-history-only queries, and `run tail --logs` separation semantics.\n- [ ] `cargo test` and `cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings` pass.\n\n## Files to Modify/Create\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/project_run_record/mod.rs` - expose the context surface, core ports, and public use cases\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/project_run_record/model.rs` - define project records, run snapshots, journal events, payload/artifact records, runtime-log records, and rollback metadata\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/project_run_record/service.rs` - implement create/list/show/delete and run query use cases with invariant checks\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/project_run_record/queries.rs` - build canonical read models for status, history, and tail\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/project_run_record/journal.rs` - define append/read ordering and sequence validation for `journal.ndjson`\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/adapters/fs.rs` - add atomic project staging, canonical snapshot reads/writes, NDJSON append helpers, prompt hashing, and active-project clearing on delete\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/project.rs` - replace stubs for `create`, `list`, `show`, and `delete` while preserving existing `select`\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/run.rs` - implement `status`, `history`, and `tail`; keep `start`, `resume`, and `rollback` as later-slice work\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/error.rs` - add duplicate-project, corrupt-record, invalid-prompt, active-run-delete, and journal-sequence error variants\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/project_records.feature` - public scenarios for project CRUD and immutable flow\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/run_queries.feature` - public scenarios for status/history/tail and runtime-log separation\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/project_run_record_test.rs` - domain and service tests for project/run invariants\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/journal_test.rs` - journal ordering, corruption, and append semantics\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/query_test.rs` - durable-history and runtime-log separation tests\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/cli.rs` - CLI integration coverage for project and run query commands\n\n## Dependencies\n- Requires: Loop 1 foundation, Loop 2 stage contract registry and deterministic rendering, Loop 3 workspace governance effective config and active project resolution\n- Blocks: Agent-driven `run start` orchestration, resume/retry/rollback semantics, and requirements-to-project handoff\n\n---\n===== /root/new-ralph-burning/.ralph/projects/ralph-burning-rewrite/loops/005-agent-execution-facade/20260311214221-spec.md\n---\nartifact: spec\nloop: 5\nproject: ralph-burning-rewrite\nbackend: claude(opus)\nrole: planner\ncreated_at: 2026-03-11T21:42:21Z\n---\n\nNow I have a clear picture. Loops 1-4 covered delivery roadmap items 1-4. The next item is **#5: Agent Execution Facade with Structured-Output Guarantee**.\n\n# Feature: Agent Execution Facade\n\n## Description\nImplement the `agent_execution` bounded context as the uniform invocation layer for all backend interactions. This context provides a structured-output guarantee: every backend call either produces a validated stage-payload-compatible result or fails with an explicit failure class. The facade abstracts backend families (Claude, Codex, OpenRouter), resolves per-role model/backend selection, enforces timeout and cancellation semantics, normalizes raw backend output into a standard invocation envelope, and preserves raw output in runtime logs. This is a prerequisite for `run start` (roadmap item 6) and must define clean port boundaries so actual backend adapters can be plugged in without changing the facade contract.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Define `BackendSpec` and `ModelSpec` types representing a backend family + model identifier, with display names and capability metadata\n- [ ] Define `BackendRole` enum mapping stage requirements to backend selection (e.g., `Planner`, `Implementer`, `Reviewer`, `QaValidator`, `CompletionJudge`) with per-role default backend/model\n- [ ] Implement `BackendResolver` that resolves the effective backend+model for a given role using precedence: explicit model override → project config → workspace default → role default\n- [ ] Define `InvocationRequest` struct containing: target stage contract reference, role, resolved backend+model, prompt/context payload, timeout duration, and cancellation token\n- [ ] Define `InvocationEnvelope` (the normalized result) containing: raw output reference, parsed structured payload (`serde_json::Value`), invocation metadata (duration, token counts, model used, attempt number), and timestamp\n- [ ] Define `AgentExecutionPort` trait with async methods: `check_capability(backend, stage_contract) -> Result<()>`, `check_availability(backend) -> Result<()>`, `invoke(request) -> Result<InvocationEnvelope>`, and `cancel(invocation_id) -> Result<()>`\n- [ ] Implement `AgentExecutionService` that orchestrates: capability verification → availability check → invocation → raw output preservation → structured output extraction → envelope construction\n- [ ] Map every failure scenario to the correct `FailureClass`: transport errors → `TransportFailure`, malformed output → `SchemaValidationFailure`, semantic issues → `DomainValidationFailure`, deadline exceeded → `Timeout`, user/system cancel → `Cancellation`\n- [ ] Cancellation token propagation: when cancel is signaled, immediately halt any in-progress invocation and return `FailureClass::Cancellation` — no further retries\n- [ ] Timeout enforcement: invocations that exceed their deadline are terminated and return `FailureClass::Timeout` — no further retries for this attempt\n- [ ] Raw backend output is written to `runtime/backend/` under the project directory via `RuntimeLogStorePort` (or a new `RawOutputPort`); never promoted to durable history\n- [ ] Session reuse: define `SessionPolicy` (enum: `NewSession`, `ReuseIfAllowed`) on `InvocationRequest`; the port checks backend/role support before reusing\n- [ ] `sessions.json` integration: persist and load session metadata per project for backends that support session continuity\n- [ ] Implement a `StubBackendAdapter` (in `adapters/`) that implements `AgentExecutionPort` with deterministic canned responses for each stage contract — sufficient for testing the full invocation pipeline without real API calls\n- [ ] Wire `AgentExecutionService` into the CLI module structure (no new CLI commands, but the service must be constructible from the existing adapter/config wiring)\n- [ ] Unit tests: capability check success/failure, resolution precedence, timeout behavior, cancellation propagation, failure class mapping, envelope construction, session policy enforcement\n- [ ] Adapter contract test for `StubBackendAdapter` verifying it satisfies `AgentExecutionPort`\n\n## Files to Modify/Create\n- `src/shared/domain.rs` — Add `BackendSpec`, `ModelSpec`, `BackendRole`, `SessionPolicy` types\n- `src/contexts/agent_execution/mod.rs` — Module root with re-exports, `CONTEXT_NAME`\n- `src/contexts/agent_execution/model.rs` — `InvocationRequest`, `InvocationEnvelope`, `InvocationMetadata`, `CancellationToken`, `CapabilityCheck` types\n- `src/contexts/agent_execution/service.rs` — `AgentExecutionService` orchestration logic, `AgentExecutionPort` trait, `BackendResolver` with precedence chain\n- `src/contexts/agent_execution/session.rs` — `SessionManager` for session reuse logic and `sessions.json` read/write\n- `src/adapters/stub_backend.rs` — `StubBackendAdapter` implementing `AgentExecutionPort` with canned payloads per stage\n- `src/adapters/mod.rs` — Register `stub_backend` module\n- `src/shared/error.rs` — Add agent execution error variants (`BackendUnavailable`, `CapabilityMismatch`, `InvocationFailed`, `InvocationTimeout`, `InvocationCancelled`)\n- `tests/unit/agent_execution_test.rs` — Unit tests for service, resolver, failure mapping\n- `tests/unit/stub_backend_test.rs` — Adapter contract tests\n- `tests/unit.rs` — Register new test modules\n\n## Dependencies\n- Requires: Loop 4 (Project and Run Record Foundation) — for `RuntimeLogStorePort`, project directory structure, `FailureClass` enum, stage contract types\n- Requires: Loop 2 (Stage Contract Registry) — for `StageContract` and `StageId` used in capability checks and payload validation\n- Requires: Loop 3 (Workspace Governance) — for workspace config defaults (`default_backend`, `default_model`) used in resolution precedence\n- Blocks: Loop 6 (Standard preset vertical path / `run start` end-to-end) — which needs the execution facade to drive stage invocations\n- Blocks: Loop 7 (Retry/remediation) — which needs failure class semantics from this facade\n\n---\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
